    "/v1/{emailAddress}/emails": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Operations on Email messages"
        ],
        "summary": "Searches emails from a specific email address. The address is specified in the {emailAddress} parameter.",
        "operationId": "listEmailsByAddressUsingGET",
        "consumes": [
          "application/json"
        ],
        "produces": [
          "*/*"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "emailAddress",
            "in": "path",
            "description": "emailAddress",
            "required": true,
            "type": "string"
          },
          {
            "name": "X-Correlation-ID",
            "in": "header",
            "description": "The value of the X-Correlation-ID header is used for correlating distributed actions in the log file.",
            "type": "string",
            "required": false
          },
          {
            "name": "Authorization",
            "in": "header",
            "description": "Json web token.",
            "type": "string",
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "$filter",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "type": "string",
            "description": "<p>The $filter querystring parameter allows clients to filter a collection of resources that are addressed by a request URL. The expression specified with $filter is evaluated for each resource in the collection, and only items where the expression evaluates to true are included in the response. Resources for which the expression evaluates to false or to null, or which reference properties that are unavailable due to permissions, are omitted from the response.<br /><br /></p>\n<p>Example: return all emails whose text contains the words 'hello' and 'world'<br /><br /></p>\n<pre><code>GET /v1/{emailAddress}/emails?$filter=text eq hello+world and tags.my_tag_name eq my_tag_value</code></pre><br /><br />\n<p>The value of the $filter option is a Boolean expression.<br /><br /></p>\n<p>Services that support $filter SHOULD support the following minimal set of operations.<br /><br /></p>\n<table>\n  <tr><td>Comparison operators</td><td></td><td></td></tr>\n  <tr><td>eq</td><td>Equal</td><td>subject eq 'Redmond'</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>ne</td><td>Not equal</td><td>city ne 'London'</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>gt</td><td>Greater than</td><td>price gt 10</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>ge</td><td>Greater than or equal</td><td>price ge 20</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>lt</td><td>Less than</td><td>price lt 10</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>le</td><td>Less than or equal</td><td>price le 20</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>Logical operators</td><td></td><td></td></tr>\n  <tr><td>and</td><td>Logical and</td><td>price le 200 and price gt 3.5</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>or</td><td>Logical or</td><td>price le 3.5 or price gt 200</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>not</td><td>Logical negation</td><td>not price le 3.5</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>Grouping operators</td><td></td><td></td></tr>\n  <tr><td>( )</td><td>Precedence grouping</td><td>(priority eq 1 or city eq 'Redmond') and price gt 100</td></tr>\n</table>"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "OK",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "$ref": "#/definitions/EmailDto"
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Bad request",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/ApiError"
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized"
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Forbidden"
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Not Found"
          }
        }
      },
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Operations on Email messages"
        ],
        "summary": "Send an email from a specific email address. The address is specified in the {emailAddress} parameter.",
